title: Symphony Finance
body:
Project Description:
Symphony Finance is building a non-custodial, interest-bearing, decentralized limit order application. Users can create yield-generating limit orders on Symphony Finance by depositing sell assets, and then while the user's funds are on the "order book" Symphony Finance's smart contracts will deposit those funds into yield-bearing strategies, until the price constraints are met that the user has specified. The strategies used to generate yield for the depositors will include multiple protocols, one of which at launch will be mStable's SAVE product. Symphony Finance will initially launch on Polygon, with plans to eventually launch on the Ethereum mainnet later this year.

Funding Objective:
Help cover the costs of smart contract audits and engineering resources. 

Funding Schedule:
$10,000 immediately
$10,000 after the public launch of Symphony Finance on Polygon
